{{Infobox language |name=Kayupulau |nativename= |states=[[Indonesia]] |region=[[Papua (province)|Papua]] |ethnicity= |speakers=50 |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Western Oceanic languages|Western Oceanic]] |fam5=[[North New Guinea languages|North New Guinea]] |fam6=[[Sarmi – Jayapura Bay languages|Sarmi – Jayapura Bay]] |fam7=[[Jayapura Bay languages|Jayapura Bay]] |iso3=kzu |glotto=kayu1243 |glottorefname=Kayupulau }}
'''Kayupulau''' is a nearly extinct [[Austronesian language]] spoken mainly by adults in [[Jayapura]] Harbor in [[Papua (Indonesian province)|Papua]] province, [[Indonesia]]. By 2007, it was used by less than a tenth of the ethnic population.<ref name=e18/>
