{{Infobox language |name=Landoma |nativename= |states=[[Guinea]] |region= |speakers={{sigfig|14400|2}} |date=1991 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Mel languages|Mel]] |fam4=Temne |fam5=[[Baga languages|Baga]] |iso3=ldm |glotto=land1256 |glottorefname=Landoma }}
'''Landoma''' (Landouman, Landuma), or ''Cocoli'', is a language of western [[Guinea]]. It is the most populous of the [[Baga languages]], in the [[Mel languages|Mel]] branch of the [[Niger–Congo languages|Niger–Congo]] language family. It is related to [[Temne language|Temne]] of Sierra Leone.
The language sometimes goes by the name of one of its dialects, Tiapi (Tyapi, Tyopi) a.k.a. Tapessi.
