'''Lucy Takiora Lord''' (c.1842 &ndash; 3 September 1893) was a New Zealand guide and interpreter. She was born in [[Russell, New Zealand|Russell]], [[Northland Region|Northland]], [[New Zealand]]. She was the daughter of the maori Kotiro Hinerangi and the English shop owner William Lord and known for her service and interpreter for the British, first during the war of the 1860s, and then during the land purchases of maori land. <ref name="DNZB Lord">{{DNZB|title=Lucy Takiora Lord|first= Mary|last= Donald|id=1l9|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

