'''Sedang''' is an [[Austroasiatic languages|Austro-Asiatic language]] spoken in eastern [[Laos]] and [[Kon Tum Province]] in south central [[Vietnam]]. The Sedang language has the most speakers of any of the languages of the [[North Bahnaric language]] group, a group of languages known for their range of [[vowel]] [[phonation]]s.

